data.text:
D-Day Veteran Wally Harris MM, 91, who fought on Gold Beach in Normandy on D-Day and was part of the force that liberated Brussells for which he won the Military Medal for Gallantry, outside St Paul's Cathedral in London. He came to tell the protesters to move their tents for Remembrance Sunday so they can hold the traditional service.
